reviews.text:
We called the restaurant to see if there was space for dinner,and the staff said there was no space,someone booked the whole place.The staff said DONT COME.

Then after we ate dinner we went to the restaurant/shop to see an “exhibition “ called Dino Experience Museum.When we went in,there was nothing to see.There wasn’t even an exhibition hall.There were seven “areas” there though.The first was a phonics game where you needed to say “Tyrannosaurus rex “to win. On an ipad.The second was a very small statue of a T. rex.There were no bones,and there was only one statue of a Dino.Barely no stuff to see.

We also decided to take a look at the restaurant.We looked into the place through the door.It was empty.Didn’t looked like someone had used the place at all.Suddenly a staff said:WE’RE CLOSED.WHAT ARE YOU LOOKING AT?! rudely. So basically nothing.Wasted our time.Dont come here.

Fun evening with the kids. Food is pretty delicious and price is reasonable. This playroom restaurant is definitely designed with real understand of kids (unlike some other more famous playroom restaurant). Will definitely come again in the future. The only thing that is keeping me from giving a 5 star is the annoying tv screen (with cartoons)  embedded inside the table which the staff claim they cannot turn off. 

Tips: let your kids wear non-slip socks if possible as they may run around and socks can make the floor quite slippery.
Looking forward to this new cafe

小朋友放電一流，食物尚算可以，不過選擇小

result.name: Discovery Park

reviews.text: Excellent place for family with kids. Can spend all day here with reasonable cost. Public facilities, shops and entertainment are all well designed with kids in mind. The cinema is even decorated and provided with kids seats and play areas. Coming place is more spacious than you could imagine.
Large mall with wide variety of shops, restaurants, and a cinema, but no supermarket. Great place for families with young kids. Parking is relatively cheap.
Good location, family friendly! Good for shopping with kids

A large and well designed shopping mall. Shops were of large types and properly located at different areas of the mall. Food choices were absurd with a bizarre choice from local fast food to American tastes to top-of-the-class cuisines. A huge recommendation for foodies. Activities there are also never-ending and makes the mall suitable for children and adults of all ages.
Spacious.  Good restaurants.  Convenient supermarket.  Comfortable weeknight visit.
